Enhancement: Improve resilience of local backend to (system) crashes

restic now ensures that files stored using the `local` backend are created
atomically, that is files are either stored completely or not at all. This
ensures that no incomplete files are left behind even if restic is terminated
while writing a file.

In addition, restic now ensures that the directory containing the newly
uploaded file is also written to disk. This can prevent missing files if
the system crashes or the disk is not properly unmounted.

